claim.claim-text:
12. A method of installing storm shutters for protecting a window, comprising the steps of: 
determining a length of an area of the window to be protected; 
slidably connecting a first panel to a second panel; 
retaining the second panel relative to the first panel at a predetermined position corresponding to the length of the area of the window to be protected by the storm shutter.

14. A removable and adjustable storm shutter for covering a section of a window by attaching the storm shutter to the window, the storm shutter comprising: 
a first rectangular panel; 
a second corresponding sized panel slidably connected to the first panel for adjusting a longitudinal length of the first and second panels; 
a first retainer for fixing the first panel relative to the second panel to set the longitudinal length of the first and second panels so that the panels extend between the upper and lower edges of the window and cover the section of the window behind the panels; and 
a second retainer along longitudinal sides of the first and second panels for interlocking the first and second panels with an adjacent set of first and second panels covering an adjacent section of the window.
